<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-039-046 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 444 765</DOCID><JOURNAL>EDGE: Work-Group Computing Report  Oct 7 1991 v2 n72 p52(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT EDGE Publishing 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Cutbacks: Dallas Semiconductor reduces work force.andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Dallas Semiconductor Corp. (Personnel management).andO;Topic:     Work Force ReductionBusiness PlanningFinancial Stability.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Dallas Semiconductor Corp. Thursday announced a 9 percent reduction in forceaffecting approximately 75 employees.andM;C.V.andP;  Prothro, president and chief executive officer of the company, statedthat:  &quot;Our sales continue to be soft, and there is not any indication that aturnaround will occur before early next year.andP;  While this decision wasdifficult, the company is attempting to maintain its profit margins withoutimpairing its ability to meet product demand.&quot;andM;Included in the reduction were 15 temporary, 35 hourly and 26 salariedemployees.andP;  Reductions came principally in the manufacturing andmanufacturing support areas.andP;  &quot;Product development will continue as in thepast and we remain confident that when the economy rebounds the company willbe well positioned to meet the expected increased demand,&quot; Prothro indicated.andM;The company announced last month that 1991 third quarter results would bebelow expectations and would be comparable to third quarter results lastyear.andP;  The company believes the slowdown in the semiconductor industry willcontinue at least through the remainder of 1991 and adversely affect thecompany's fourth quarter results.andM;Prothro said, &quot;The steps taken today will lessen the adverse impact on ourprofitability during this no growth period.&quot;andO;</TEXT></DOC>